          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C (160°C fan). Line a 900 g (2 lb) loaf tin with baking paper. Beat {{unsalted-butter}} and {{caster-sugar}} until pale and fluffy. Add the {{lemon}} zest. Beat in the {{eggs}} one at a time. Fold in {{self-raising-flour}}, then stir in the {{poppy-seeds}} and {{whole-milk}}. Scrape into the tin and bake for 40 to 45 minutes until a skewer comes out clean.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Drizzle while hot",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Stir the drizzle {{lemon-juice}} and {{caster-sugar}} together in a small bowl, don't heat it. The moment the cake comes out of the oven, poke it all over with a skewer, going right to the bottom. Pour the drizzle slowly and evenly over the surface. Leave in the tin until completely cool. The drizzle needs time to set into the crust before the cake is moved.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
